    "Also, although the general time series methods (TimesNet, OFA, FITS) perform well in other time series tasks, they struggle to outperform methods specifically designed for anomaly detection tasks like LSTMAD and FCVAE (RI 13).",
    "This may indicate that there is a gap between time series anomaly detection tasks and general time representation tasks.",
    "For example, anomaly detection tasks may require models to have a stronger denoising effect.",
    "These gaps need special attention when designing models for anomaly detection tasks.",
    "C. Performance under Delay-ConstraintIssue d in Sec."
